      "english": "{0:Now}, {1:finding the occasion}, {4:Arjuna} {5:speaks} {3:in order to learn} {2:the marks of the man of settled wisdom} — {16:taking it} {8:that, for} {7:the very} {10:marks} {6:which} are {9:of those liberated-while-living}, {11:those} {12:very ones} are, {13:for seekers of release}, {14:the means to liberation}{15:}. He {24:whose} {23:prajñā} {19:‘I} {21:am} {20:Brahman’} {17:stands} {18:unmoving} is {26:the sthita-prajña}, {27:possessed of two states}: {28:established-in-samādhi} and {29:risen-up (active)}{30:}. {32:Hence} {33:he qualifies} it: {34:of the one in samādhi}, {35:the sthita-prajña}, {36:what} is the {37:‘speech’}? — {39:a genitive} {38:in the sense of object}. {43:‘bhāṣā’} is {44:the mark} {40:by which he is described} {41:by this}{42:}. The {52:sense}: {47:by what} {48:mark} is {46:the sthita-prajña}, {45:settled in samādhi}, {50:referred to} {49:by others}{51:}? {53:And he} {55:who has risen up}, {56:the steady-minded one}, {57:the sthita-prajña} — {59:what} does he {58:himself} {60:say}? {61:Amid praise and blame and the like}, {63:what} {62:marks of rejoicing, dveṣa and the like} does he {64:how} {65:show}? — {68:the optative} {66:throughout} {67:in the sense of supposition}{69:}. {70:‘How} does he {71:sit}?’{72:} — {73:to restrain the risen-up mind}, {74:how} does he {77:effect the restraint} of the {75:outer} {76:indriyas}? {79:When that restraint is absent}, {80:‘how} does he {81:move’} — {82:how} does he {84:approach} {83:objects}? {85:His speaking, sitting and moving}, that are {86:unlike the ignorant crowd}, {87:of what sort are they}{88:}? — {89:that is the meaning}{90:}. {91:Thus} there are {92:four} {93:questions}: {96:one} {94:about the one in samādhi}, {95:the sthita-prajña}, {99:three} {97:about the risen-up} {98:sthita-prajña}{100:}. {103:By addressing him} {101:‘Keśava’}{102:}, he {113:hints}: {105:‘You} {106:alone}, {104:as the inner controller of all}, {110:are able} {109:to tell} {107:such} {108:a secret’}{111:}{112:}.",
