      "english": "{0:His movement and other activity} is {1:not} {2:preceded by excessive deliberate intent}, {3:like the activity of a madman and so on} — {8:intending to show} this {7:by ‘yā niśā’ and so on} later, he {10:first} {11:states} {9:the mark} {12:by ‘prajahāti’}. The drift of {21:the question}: {14:being thus} {15:satisfied in supreme bliss}, {16:why} {19:does he} {17:thus} engage in {18:activity} at all? {29:With the intent} that, {23:for one whose Brahman is slightly veiled} {22:by commenced karma}, {26:an activity with little deliberate intent} {25:generally} {27:arises} {24:through latent impressions}, he {30:resolves} it. He {33:abandons} {31:‘almost’} {32:all} — {35:for even} {34:in Śuka and the rest} {36:a little is seen}; since {42:it is said}, {39:‘the knowers}, {40:the seers of truth}, {38:desire} {37:devotion to your feet’}, they {44:desire} {43:that}. {45:When} {48:insistence} {47:in Indra and the others} {49:is seen}, {50:then} {52:their} {53:knowledge} is {51:overcome}. {56:As stated}: {57:‘In men of office}, {59:by reason of their great karmic load}, {60:arising and overcoming} occur {61:in knowledge}; {62:thereby} {64:they differ} {63:from others’}. {66:Hence} {67:just} {68:by such difference}, {71:if} {70:insistence and the like} {72:there be} {69:in the unqualified}, {74:they} {73:are not} {75:knowers} {76:—} {77:that should be understood}. {79:Nor} {84:is} {83:the mark} {80:here} being stated {82:of one engaged in} {81:samādhi}, {89:since affection is denied} by {85:‘he who} is {87:without affection} {86:everywhere’}{88:}; {91:for} {96:there is} {90:no} {95:encountering of good or ill} {94:for him} {93:engaged in} {92:samādhi} — {97:that being unconscious samādhi}; {98:in the conscious} samādhi {99:though} {100:there is no contradiction}, {101:so} {102:even then} {103:there is no} {107:fixed rule} {105:that it be} {104:only} {106:there}. As the {118:smṛti says}: {108:‘kāmas and the rest} {109:do not} {110:arise} {112:even} {111:indeed} {113:in the distracted-minded} {114:knowers}, {115:whose impurities are burnt away by knowledge}, {116:through resort to the Lord’}. {121:kāmas} are {120:indeed} {119:manas-seated}; {122:hence}, {123:in that} {124:very} mind, {125:when a knowledge opposed to them arises}, {127:the relinquishment} {128:of them} {126:is fitting} {129:—} he {130:shows} this {131:by ‘mano-gatān’}. {133:The opposition} {134:too} {135:is stated}: {136:‘his rasa} {137:too} {141:turns away} {140:on seeing} {139:the Supreme’} {138:in him}. {144:And} {145:this} {147:is not to be explained away as fruitless} {146:without that seeing}, {148:because of the distinction among persons}. {149:‘By the Self’} means {150:by the Supreme Self}; {153:established} {151:in the Supreme Self} {152:alone} {154:being}; {157:for one established} {156:in That} {155:called the Self}, {160:contentment} {161:arises} {158:from His grace} {159:alone}, as in the {176:Nārāyaṇa-Rāma-kalpa}: {164:‘having given up} {162:the objects}, {166:for one established} {165:in Rāma}, {167:thereupon} {170:contentment} {169:comes} {168:from the Lord} {171:and not} {172:otherwise} {173:but} {174:in any way whatsoever’} {175:—}. {177:Therefore} {179:the self} is {178:not} {180:the individual soul}.",
