      "english": "{0:Although} the {4:indriyas} — namely the {1:‘objects’}, {3:denoted by the word ‘objects’}, that is, {2:indicated by their objects} — {12:turn away}, even for {5:the abstinent}, {6:one whose objects are not being drawn in}, even for {10:a fool} {9:established} {7:in harsh} {8:austerity}, {13:of the embodied one}, {14:possessed of a body} — yet {15:‘leaving out the rasa’}: {16:rasa}, {19:which} is {17:rāga} {18:toward objects} — {20:that} {21:leaving aside}. {22:The word “rasa”} {24:is well known} {23:in the sense of rāga} — {26:“proceeding} {25:by his own rasa”}, {27:“the relisher}, {28:the connoisseur”}, {29:and} {30:so on are seen}. {31:That} {33:rasa} {32:too}, {34:of the nature of coloring}, {35:subtle}, {36:of this} {37:ascetic}, {41:on seeing} — {42:on apprehending} — {38:the Supreme}, {39:the truth of the highest reality}, {40:Brahman} — {47:abiding} {43:as ‘I} am {44:verily} {45:That’}{46:} — {48:turns away}; the {50:cognition of objects} {51:becomes} {49:seedless}, {52:that is} {53:the meaning}. {54:Not}, {55:in the absence of} {56:right vision}, is there {58:the cutting off} {57:of the rasa}. {59:Therefore} {62:the steadiness} {61:of the prajñā} {60:whose nature is right vision} {63:should be made} {64:—} {65:this is the import}.",
