      "english": "{0:But surely} {2:even} {1:in a fool}, {3:by reason of disease and the like}, there is {6:a withdrawal} {5:of the indriyas} {4:from objects} {7:—} {8:that being so}, {9:how} {14:was it said} that {10:his} {11:prajñā} {12:stands firm} {13:?} {15:To this} {16:He says} {17:‘viṣayāḥ’} {18:—}. {19:Of the abstinent} — one who {21:by the indriyas} {23:does not take in} {22:objects} {20:—}, {24:of the embodied one} {25:possessed of the conceit of the body}, {27:even} {26:of a fool}, {28:a sick man}, {30:or} {29:one of wooden austerity}, {31:the objects}, {32:sound and the rest}, {33:turn away}; {34:but} {35:‘leaving out the rasa’} — {36:the tṛṣṇā that is rasa}, {37:that} {38:leaving aside}. {39:For the ignorant} {40:the objects} {41:turn away}, {44:but} {43:the rāga} {42:directed at them} {45:does not} {46:turn away} {47:—} that is {48:the meaning}. {50:But} {49:for this} {51:sthita-prajña}, who, {54:having seen} {52:the supreme} {53:human goal} and {60:directly realized} {55:‘That} {56:very thing} {57:am} {58:I’}, {59:thus} {61:abides}, {62:the rasa} {63:too} — {65:even} {64:the rāga toward petty pleasure} — {66:turns away}. {67:From the word ‘api’ (‘too’)}, {68:the objects} {69:also} turn away. {71:And} {70:so} {76:it has been explained} under {72:‘yāvān} {73:arthaḥ’} {74:} {75:and the rest}. {78:And} {77:thus} {79:the turning-away of object-along-with-rāga} is {80:the mark of the sthita-prajña}, {81:so} {82:there is no} {84:over-extension} {83:to the fool} {85:—} that is {86:the meaning}. {87:Since} {88:without} {90:right vision of the Supreme Self} {89:there is no} {91:rooting-out of object-along-with-rāga}, {92:therefore} one should, {97:with great} {98:effort}, {99:bring about} {96:the steadiness} {95:of the prajñā} {94:that is right vision} and {93:that roots out object-along-with-rāga} {100:—} this is {101:the import}.",
