      "english": "{0:But surely} {4:the non-engagement} {2:of the indriyas} {3:with objects} {8:can}{1:not} {7:be} {6:the mark} {5:of the sthita-prajña}, {15:since there is no difference} {14:in the non-engagement} {13:with objects} {9:of the dull}, {10:the sick}, {12:and} {11:those given to fasting}. {16:To that} {17:He says}, {19:with} {18:‘viṣayāḥ’}. {22:The taking-in}, {23:the grasping}, {21:of objects} {20:by the indriyas}, is {24:‘āhāra’ (intake)}. {25:Of the abstinent}, {28:who does not perform} {27:the grasping of objects} {26:by the indriyas}, {29:of the embodied one} {30:possessed of body-conceit}, {31:of the ignorant}, {32:rāga}, {33:that is, craving} — {34:leaving that out}; {35:his craving} {36:does not} {37:turn away}, {38:that is} {39:the meaning}. {40:Or}: {41:of the abstinent}, {42:one given to fasting}, {43:the objects} {44:for the most part} {45:turn away}, {47:since, scorched by hunger, he has no expectation of sound, touch and the rest}{46:}, {48:but} {49:‘leaving out the rasa’}, {50:the expectation of rasa} {51:however} {52:does not} {53:turn away} — {54:that is} {55:the meaning}. {56:The rest} {57:is the same}.",
