      "english": "{0:Of one striving} — {1:making} {1:effort} — {3:for}, {4:since}; {5:O son of Kuntī}, {6:of a man}, {9:even} {7:of one who is wise}, {8:discerning} — {12:the construction connects} {11:across the intervening words}. {13:The indriyas}, {14:churning, agitating}, {15:of a churning nature} — {17:for} they {19:violently agitate}, {20:throw into turmoil}, {16:a man turned toward the objects}, {21:and, having thrown him into turmoil}, {22:and} {23:they carry off} {24:by force}, {25:overpowering him}, {26:in open view} {27:indeed}, {30:the manas} {28:of one who is looking on}, {29:the mind endowed with discriminative knowledge}.",
