      "english": "{0:There}, {1:for the firmness of prajñā}, {2:reining in the outer indriyas} and {3:reining in the manas} {4:together} are {5:the special} {6:cause}, since {7:in the absence of both} {8:the destruction of prajñā is seen} {9:—} so, {10:to state} {12:the first} {13:fault} {11:in the absence of reining in the outer indriyas}, {14:He says} {15:‘yatataḥ’} {16:—}. {17:O} {18:son of Kuntī}! {19:Of a man striving} — {24:making} {23:the effort} {22:that consists in seeing} {20:again} {21:and again} the fault in the objects — {25:even} {36:of one exceedingly discerning}, {44:the indriyas} {45:carry off}, {47:bring} {46:to modification}, {39:the manas}, {43:even when} it has been {42:made} {41:unmodified} {40:for a mere instant}. ({26:cakṣ}, {27:by the making of the ṅ-marker}, {28:as anudātta-marked}, {29:has the middle voice non-obligatory}; {31:thus} {32:from this indication} {33:the active voice} {34:is not inconsistent}.) {48:But surely}, {50:when discrimination}, {49:contrary} as it is, {51:is present}, {52:whence} {53:the arising of modification}? {54:To that} {55:He says} {56:‘pramāthīni’}, {57:of a churning nature}, {58:by reason of their exceeding strength} {59:able to crush discrimination}. {60:Hence} {61:‘by force’}, {62:forcibly}, {63:by sheer violence}, {64:even while he is looking on} {65:—} {66:even while the discerning man}, {67:the master}, {68:and discrimination}, {69:and} {70:the protector}, {71:are present}, {74:the indriyas}, {72:by churning everything} {73:indeed}, {81:carry off} {77:the manas} {76:that has entered} {75:the discrimination-born prajñā}, {79:dislodging} it {78:from there} and {80:making it possessed by their own object} {82:—} that is {83:the meaning}. {84:The word “for”} {86:lights up} {85:the well-known fact}; {88:for} {89:this} {90:matter} is {87:well known} {91:in the world}: {92:just as} {93:churning} {94:robbers}, {95:by force} {96:indeed}, {100:overpowering} {97:the rich man} {98:and the wealth-guard} {99:and}, {105:carry off} {104:the wealth} {102:while} {101:those two} look on {103:even}, {106:so} {107:the indriyas} {108:too}, {109:in the proximity of the objects}, {111:carry off} {110:the manas} {112:—}.",
