      "english": "{0:‘With rāga and dveṣa gone’} — {1:rāga} {2:and} {3:dveṣa}, {5:the rāga-and-dveṣa pair}; {9:the engagement} {8:of the indriyas} is {10:natural}, {6:preceded by them} {7:indeed}. {11:There}, {12:the one} {15:who} {13:is a seeker of release} {14:becomes}, by {19:indriyas} — {18:hearing and the rest} — {17:freed} {16:of those two}, {22:engaging} {21:the unavoidable} {20:objects}, {23:apprehending them}, by {30:indriyas under the Self’s control} {24:by those under the Self’s control} — {25:of the Self} {26:the controllable ones}, {27:that have become subject}, {28:the indriyas}, {29:by those} — {31:he whose inner organ is governable} {32:at will}: {33:governable} {34:is the self}, {35:the inner organ}, {36:of whom} — {37:he}, {38:this one}, {40:attains} {39:serenity}. {41:‘Serenity’} is {42:clearness}, {43:well-being}.",
