      "english": "{8:Saying} that, when {0:the manas} {1:is restrained}, {2:but} there is {5:no} {6:fault} {4:even} {3:in the absence of restraint of the outer indriyas} — {7:that}, {14:He gives} {13:the answer} {12:to} ‘{9:how} {10:does he move}’ {15:in eight verses}. {16:He who}, {17:whose mind is uncomposed}, {18:he}, {20:having restrained} {21:even} {19:the outer indriyas}, {25:while pondering} {24:objects} {23:with a manas} {22:tainted by rāga and dveṣa}, {27:falls} {28:becomes} {26:from the human goal}. {29:But the governable-self one} — {31:the word ‘tu’ (but)} {33:marks the difference} {32:from the former}: but {34:he whose inner organ is mastered}, {44:by indriyas} {36:that are under the Self} ({37:subject to the manas}, i.e. {38:self-controlled}), {39:—} {40:or} {43:that are freed} {42:separated} {41:of rāga and dveṣa}, {49:engaging} {48:the non-prohibited} {46:objects}, {45:hearing and the rest}, {47:sound and the rest}, {50:apprehending} them, {56:attains} {51:serenity}, {52:the clearness} {54:the limpidity} {53:of the mind}, {55:its fitness for the direct realization of the Supreme Self}. {57:Indriyas prompted by rāga and dveṣa} {58:—} {60:become} {59:a cause of fault}; but {61:when the manas} {62:is in his control} {63:—} {64:there is no} {65:rāga and dveṣa}; {68:and} {67:in the absence} {66:of those two} {69:there is no} {70:engagement of the indriyas dependent on them}; and {73:the apprehension of objects}, {71:being unavoidable}, {76:brings} {74:no} {75:fault} — {78:so there is no} {79:obstruction to purity}, {80:that} {81:is the sense}. {82:By this} {100:the doubt} {101:is dispelled}: ‘{86:If} {85:even} {84:the mere remembering} {83:of objects} {86:be} {87:a cause of calamity}, {89:then} {88:all the more} {90:enjoyment}; {95:how}, then, {94:enjoying} {93:objects} {92:for the sake of living}, {97:does he} {98:not incur} {96:calamity}?’ {107:And} {110:by} ‘{105:he reaches} {104:objects} {103:with indriyas} {102:under his own control}’, {112:the answer} {108:to} ‘{108:how} {109:does he move}’ {114:comes} {113:to be stated}.",
