      "english": "{0:But surely}, {4:since} {3:to check} {1:the indriyas}, {2:whose nature is to incline toward objects}, {4:is impossible}, {5:this} {6:fault} is {7:hard to avert} — {8:so} {10:how} {11:can there be} {9:the state of settled wisdom}? {12:Thus} {13:anticipating}, {14:He says}, {16:} {15:‘rāga-dveṣa’} {17:in two verses}. {20:By indriyas} {18:free of rāga and dveṣa}, {19:devoid of arrogance}, {22:engaging} {21:over objects}, {23:enjoying} them, {24:he nonetheless} {27:attains} {25:serenity}, {26:peace}. {28:The freedom from rāga and dveṣa} {30:He states} {29:very} {32:} {31:‘ātma’}: {36:by indriyas} {35:under the control} {33:of the self}, {34:the manas} — {41:he whose} {39:self}, {40:the manas}, is {37:governable}, {38:subject to him}{42:.} {43:By this} {44:very thing} {55:the answer} {47:to} {48:this}, {49:the fourth question}, ‘{45:how} {46:does he move}’, {54:that is}, {57:comes to be} {56:stated}: ‘{53:he reaches} {52:objects} {51:with indriyas} {50:under his own control}.’",
