      "english": "{0:Of the indriyas} {3:ranging}, {5:engaged each in its own} {4:object} — {6:that} {7:manas} which {8:follows after}, {9:runs along after} — {10:that} {7:manas}, {12:set going} {11:by the conceptual fancy of indriya-object}, {16:robs} {14:his}, {15:this ascetic’s}, {17:prajñā}, {18:the insight born of the discrimination of Self from non-Self}, {19:destroys} it. {20:How?} {21:As wind} {22:a boat} {23:like} {25:on the water}: {30:just as} {31:wind}, {28:lifting up} {27:off its course} {32:a boat} {26:of those wishing to go} {24:on the water}, {33:drives} it {29:onto a wrong course}, {34:so} {38:the manas}, {37:having robbed} {35:the insight whose object is the Self}, {36:the prajñā}, {40:makes} it {39:an insight whose object is objects}.",
