      "sanskrit": "kathamayuktasya bhāvanā na bhavati ? āha – indriyāṇāmiti| anuvidhīyate – kriyate| nanvīśvareṇendriyāṇāmanu| ‘buddhirjñānam’ ityādi vakṣyamāṇatvāt| prajñāṃ -prajñānam| utpatsyadapi nivārayatītyarthaḥ| utpannasyāpyabhibhavo bhavati",
      "ourRendering": "How is there no contemplation for the unsteadied one? He says ‘indriyāṇām’. ‘anuvidhīyate’ — is done. ‘Surely it is by the Lord that the indriyas are…’ — because ‘understanding, knowledge’ and so on are to be spoken of (later). ‘Insight’ (prajñā) means knowledge. It even prevents what is about to arise, that is the meaning; and there is the overcoming of what has already arisen.",
