      "english": "{0:Thus}, {1:so}, {8:it was said} that {2:the seeker of release} should, {4:with effort}, {6:effect} {5:the reining-in of the indriyas} {3:for the firmness of prajñā}; {10:but} {9:for the sthita-prajña} {14:the reining-in of all the indriyas} {12:is accomplished} {13:of its own accord} {11:of itself} — {16:so He says} {17:‘yā} {18:niśā’}. {20:That} {26:prajñā} ‘{22:I} {23:am} {23:Brahman}{24:,}’ {21:of the form of the direct realization born of the Vedānta-sentence}, {30:is}, {27:for all beings}, {28:the ignorant}, {30:like} {29:night} — {31:night} — {34:since toward} {33:them} {32:it} {34:is of an unillumined nature}. {35:In that} {37:night-of-all-beings} {36:marked by the knowledge of Brahman}, ‘{38:he keeps watch}’: {40:awakened} {39:from the sleep of ignorance}, {41:being so} {43:he abides} {42:attentive} — {44:the one who reins himself in}, {45:possessed of the reining-in of the indriyas}, {46:the sthita-prajña}, {47:that} {48:is the meaning}. {50:But} {49:that wherein}, {52:in the sleep of ignorance} {51:marked by the dualistic view}, {55:beings}, {53:though verily asleep} {54:—}, ‘{56:are awake}’ — {58:they carry on their dealings} {57:like dreamers} — {59:that} {60:is night}: {61:it does} {62:not shine} {66:for the sage}, {67:the sthita-prajña}, {64:who sees}, {65:directly}, {63:the truth of the Self}. {69:For} {68:so long as} one is {70:not} {71:awakened}, {72:just so long} {73:alone} {72:does} {74:dream-seeing} {72:last}, {75:since} {76:error} reaches only as far as the awakening; {78:but} {77:at the time of the knowledge of truth} {79:there is no} {81:single} {82:dealing} {80:occasioned by error}. {83:That} {84:is stated} {85:by the author of the Vārtika}: ‘{86:in the transaction of agency} {87:indeed} {88:the pure} {89:reality} {90:is not} {91:beheld}; {95:and} {94:when} {92:the pure} {93:reality} {94:is established}, {96:the busying with agency} {97:so too} ceases.’ ‘{98:Like crow and owl} {99:is} {100:this} {101:saṃsāra} {102:for the ignorant and the knower of the Self}; {109:Hari} {108:himself} {107:declared} “{103:what} {104:is night} {105:for all beings}”{106:.}’ {112:And so}, {113:of him who} has {114:the contrary view} {115:—} {116:there is not} {117:the seeing of the reality}, {119:since} {118:the contrary view} {119:is born of the non-seeing of the reality}; {121:and} {120:of him who} has {122:the seeing of the reality} {123:—} {124:there is not} {125:the contrary view}, {129:since} {126:the cause of the contrary view}, {127:the non-seeing of the reality}, {129:is sublated} {128:by the seeing of the reality}. {130:So too} {132:the śruti}: ‘{133:Where} {135:there is} {134:duality} {136:as it were}, {138:there} {139:one} {141:sees} {140:another}; {142:but where}, {144:for him}, {145:everything} {146:has become} {147:the very} {146:Self}, {149:then} {150:by what} {152:should one see} {151:whom}?’ {153:—} {156:He declares} {155:the settled distinction} {154:of knowledge and ignorance}. {157:Just as} {158:for the crow}, {159:night-blind}, {160:it is day}, {161:and for the owl}, {162:day-blind}, {163:it is night}, {166:and} {167:to the owl} {165:seeing} {164:by night}, {168:that which} {169:is day} {172:is}, {171:verily}, {170:night} {173:for the crow} {174:—} {177:this} {175:is a great} {176:wonder}. {178:Therefore}, {179:for the seers of truth}, {180:how} {182:could there be} {181:the ignorance-born transaction of agency and the like}? {184:So} {188:the reining-in of the indriyas} {186:is}, {187:for him}, {185:accomplished} {184:of itself} — {189:that} {190:is the meaning}.",
