      "english": "{2:Having gathered} {0:the stated} {1:mark} into a sum, he {3:says} {4:‘yā} {5:niśā’}: {7:that which} {9:is night} {8:for all beings}, {10:marked by the very nature of the Supreme Lord}, {11:wherein}, {13:as if} {12:asleep}, they {16:know} {15:nothing} {14:—} {17:in that} {19:the knower} {18:yoked to the reining-in of the indriyas} {20:keeps watch}, {23:sees} {21:rightly} and {22:directly} {24:the Supreme Self}, {26:that is the meaning}. {27:But that wherein} — {28:marked by objects} — {29:beings} {30:are awake}, {31:in that}, {33:as if} {34:asleep} {32:in the night}, he {35:for the most part} {36:does not} {37:know}; {39:his movement and other activity} is {38:like that of a madman and the like}. {40:That} {41:is stated} {51:by the two verses} {43:‘} {42:the body}, {44:that} {45:is not} {46:the last’}, {47:‘the body} {48:too} {49:is gone under the sway of fate’}. {53:‘The sage} is one {52:yoked to reflection’}; He {58:states} {57:the means} {56:for this} {54:‘seeing’ one}.",
